IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: USING THE SCIENCE OF SYSTEMS BIOLOGY TO PREDICT, PREVENT AND CURE DISEASE.
IRS990.MissionDescription: THE INSTITUTE FOR SYSTEMS BIOLOGY, A NONPROFIT RESEARCH INSTITUTE, WAS FOUNDED IN 1999 WITH THE MISSION OF TRANSFORMING BIOLOGICAL AND MEDICAL RESEARCH BY CREATING AND USING SYSTEMS APPROACHES TO UNRAVEL THE WORKINGS OF COMPLEX BIOLOGICAL SYSTEMS. THE GOAL OF THE INSTITUTE IS TO INCREASE OUR UNDERSTANDING OF THE HUMAN IMMUNE SYSTEM AND OTHER BIOLOGICAL SYSTEMS SO THAT MEDICINE CAN BECOME MORE PREDICTIVE, PREVENTATIVE AND PERSONALIZED. A DEEPER AND MORE COMPREHENSIVE UNDERSTANDING OF HOW BIOLOGICAL SYSTEMS WORK TOGETHER CAN LEAD TO THE DEVELOPMENT OF (1) NEW WAYS TO PREDICT A PATIENT'S SUSCEPTIBILITY TO A PARTICULAR DISEASE OR ILLNESS, (2) MORE EFFECTIVE DIAGNOSES AND TREATMENT FOR A VARIETY OF DISEASES, AND (3) UNIQUE AND TARGETED WELLNESS AND PREVENTION PLANS FOR EVERYONE.
IRS990.Description: BIOLOGICAL AND MEDICAL RESEARCH -- INSTITUTE FOR SYSTEMS BIOLOGY (ISB) SCIENTISTS PUBLISHED APPROXIMATELY 70 RESEARCH PAPERS IN PEER REVIEWED JOURNALS IN 2008. MAJOR AREAS OF RESEARCH FOCUS INCLUDED HIV VACCINE DEVELOPMENT, H5N1 FLU, NEUROLOGICAL DISEASE, CANCER, EARLY DIAGNOSIS OF DISEASE VIA COST EFFECTIVE BIOMARKER IDENTIFICATION AND DETECTION, DEVELOPMENT OF COMPUTATIONAL MODELS THAT PREDICT THE BEHAVIOR OF COMPLEX BIOLOGICAL SYSTEMS (WITH THE PURPOSE OF RE-ENGINEERING MALFUNCTIONING SYSTEMS BACK TO HEALTH), AND MORE. IN 2008, THOMSON SCIENTIFIC IDENTIFIED ISB AS HAVING THE 6TH HIGHEST RESEARCH IMPACT GLOBALLY BASED ON PEER-PUBLISHED PAPER CITATION BY OTHER RESEARCHERS.

Activity2.Description: SCIENCE EDUCATION -- THE INSTITUTE FOR SYSTEMS BIOLOGY'S (ISB) CENTER FOR INQUIRY SCIENCE (CIS) SUPPORTED SCIENCE EDUCATORS FROM 27 SCHOOL DISTRICTS REPRESENTING 37 PERCENT OF WASHINGTON STATE'S STUDENT POPULATION. CIS STAFF HOSTED MORE THAN 140 PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT SESSIONS ATTENDED BY NEARLY 1,000 TEACHERS OVER THE COURSE OF 255 WORKSHOP DAYS. CIS'S MISSION IS TO ENABLE EDUCATORS TO PRODUCE SCIENTIFICALLY LITERATE STUDENTS BY CREATING AND SUPPORTING COLLABORATIVE PARTNERSHIPS AMONG SCHOOLS, DISTRICTS AND COMMUNITY STAKEHOLDERS THAT ARE DESIGNED TO TRAIN AND SUPPORT SCIENCE TEACHERS.

Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.ReturnReference: Description of Intended Use of Endowment Funds:
Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: THESE ENDOWMENT FUNDS ARE PLEDGED AS COLLATERAL FOR THE ORGANIZATION'S LONG-TERM DEBT.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, line 8b
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: ALL MEETINGS HELD AND WRITTEN ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE INSTITUTE'S BOARD OF DIRECTORS ARE DOCUMENTED CONTEMPORANEOUSLY IN MINUTES. BECAUSE OF THE SMALL SIZE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS AND EVEN SMALLER SIZE OF ITS COMMITTEES, MEETINGS OF BOARD COMMITTEES HELD IN 2008 WERE NOT DOCUMENTED IN MINUTES OR OTHER FORM.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, line 10
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: FORM 990 IS PREPARED WITH ASSISTANCE FROM A PAID PROFESSIONAL ADVISOR BASED ON INFORMATION PREPARED BY STAFF. THE DRAFT RETURN IS REVIEWED IN TURN BY THE DIRECTOR OF FINANCE, THE SENIOR VICE PRESIDENT FOR FINANCE & OPERATIONS, AND THEN BY THE AUDIT COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS BEFORE COMPLETING IT IN FINAL FORM. THE FILING VERSION OF THE RETURN IS DISTRIBUTED ELECTRONICALLY TO ALL BOARD MEMBERS PRIOR TO FILING WITH THE IRS.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST (COI) POLICY APPLIES TO 'COVERED PERSONS', DEFINED AS ANY INSTITUTE (BOARD) DIRECTOR, OFFICER, OR ANY MEMBER OF ANY COMMITTEE OF THE INSTITUTE'S BOARD OF DIRECTORS THAT HAS AUTHORITY TO ACT ON BEHALF OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. EACH COVERED PERSON SHALL PROMPTLY AND FULLY DISCLOSE ALL MATERIAL FACTS OF EVERY ACTUAL OR POTENTIAL CONFLICT OF INTEREST: [A] EXISTING AT THE TIME WHEN HE/SHE BECOMES A COVERED PERSON; [B] THAT ARISES WHILE HE/SHE IS A COVERED PERSON, AT THE TIME SUCH ACTUAL OR POTENTIAL CONFLICT ARISES; AND [C] THROUGH THE ANNUAL CIRCULATION OF THE FIDUCIARY COI QUESTIONNAIRE. THE VICE PRESIDENT OF FINANCE & ADMINSTRATION SHALL DISCLOSE TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ALL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST REPORTED TO HIM OR HER UNDER THIS POLICY. THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS WILL EVALUATE THE DISCLOSURES TO DETERMINE WHETHER THEY INVOLVE ACTUAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST AND MAY ATTEMPT TO DEVELOP ALTERNATIVES TO REMOVE THE CONFLICT FROM THE SITUATION.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: DURING 2008, THE COMPENSATION OF THE INSTITUTE'S PRESIDENT WAS REVIEWED BY A PAID CONSULTANT TO DETERMINE ITS COMPARABILITY TO PREVAILING MARKET CONDITIONS FOR SIMILAR POSITIONS AT OTHER ORGANIZATIONS. THIS STUDY WAS PRESENTED TO AND APPROVED BY THE INSTITUTE'S GOVERNING BOARD OF DIRECTORS. THE PRESIDENT ABSTAINS FROM VOTING ON MATTERS RELATED TO HIS COMPENSATION. THE COMPENSATION OF THE SCIENCE DIRECTOR, VP OF FINANCE AND VP OF DEVELOPMENT ARE BASED UPON THE APPROVAL BY THE PRESIDENT.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE INSTITUTE'S GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE NOT MADE READILY AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC. THE INSTITUTE'S APPLICATION FOR TAX EXEMPT STATUS AND ITS ANNUAL FORM 990 ARE AVAILABLE FOR PUBLIC INSPECTION AND REVIEW UPON REQUEST.
THERE ARE EIGHT VOLUNTEER BOARD MEMBERS.
THE ORGANIZATION IS PART OF A CONSOLIDATED FINANCIAL STATEMENT AUDIT WHERE THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE PRESENTED IN ACCORDANCE WITH GAAP. ALSO APPLICABLE TO FORM 990, PART XI, LINE 2B.
